1 unit(s) Tofu
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
1 unit(s) Gala Apple
56 g Red Cabbage, shredded
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
1 unit(s) Honey
100 g Bacon Strips
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Sugar*

Pat tofu dry with paper towels, then crumble into pea-sized pieces onto a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 tbsp (3 tbsp) oil and BBQ Seasoning. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Bake in the middle of the oven, stirring halfway through, until golden, 17-20 min.
When tofu is done, transfer to a large bowl. Add BBQ sauce, then toss to coat.

Meanwhile, core, then cut apple into 1/4-inch matchsticks.
Drain pickles over a small bowl.
Add 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) mayo to the same bowl with pickle brine, season with pepper, then whisk to combine.
In a medium bowl, add cabbage and season with salt.
Using your hands, massage cabbage until slightly tender, 1 min.
Drizzle with brine-mayo mixture, then add apples. Toss together.

Add mustard, half the honey (use all for 4 ppl) and remaining mayo to another small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Arrange bacon strips in a single layer on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Roast bacon in the bottom of the oven until crispy and cooked through, 8-12 min.**

Halve sandwich buns.
Arrange directly on the top rack of the oven, cut-side up.
Toast buns until golden-brown, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)

Spread honey-mustard mayo on sandwich buns.
Top bottom buns with pickles, bacon and BBQ tofu. Close with top buns.
Divide BBQ tofu sandwiches and cabbage-apple slaw between plates.

If you've opted to add bacon, arrange bacon strips in a single layer on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Roast bacon in the bottom of the oven until crispy and cooked through, 8-12 min.**

Top buns with bacon.